\chapter{Introduction}
\label{ch:introduction}
\lhead{Chapter~\ref{ch:introduction}. \emph{Introduction}}

This dissertation presents a systematic design of whistle pattern recognition and classification. Classification is a key step in many studies of dolphin recognition and behavior. A robust analysis tool that automatically extract whistle information from recordings and classify them into different groups is necessary, especially when a large amount of whistles are available.

